# AI Behavior Rules

## Read Before Writing
1. Read the relevant page spec in `frontend/docs/pages/` before building any page
2. Read the component catalog before creating new components — it may already exist
3. Read the backend module doc (`docs/architecture/modules/{module}.md`) for the API contract

## Don't
- Don't create new base components when shadcn/ui has one
- Don't add `console.log` statements (use proper error boundaries or toast)
- Don't hardcode tenant-specific values — everything is multi-tenant
- Don't bypass the API client with raw `fetch()`
- Don't store sensitive data in Zustand or URL params
- Don't create components > 300 lines — split into smaller composable pieces
- Don't add features beyond what the page spec describes

## Do
- Use `<PermissionGate>` for all protected sections
- Handle loading/error/empty states in every data component
- Use the existing `DataTable` component for all tabular data
- Follow the existing query key conventions
- Use Zod schemas for all form validation
- Show monitoring toggle state clearly — if a feature is disabled, say why

## Workforce Intelligence Pages
- Always check if monitoring is enabled before showing data
- Screenshot-related UI must be gated by `monitoring:configure` or higher
- Activity data is read-only in the frontend — never POST to activity endpoints
- Exception alerts support real-time via SignalR — use `useExceptionAlerts` hook
- Self-service (`/my-dashboard`) shows own data only, NO rankings or comparisons
